There, more than 100 technicians (generally mechanical experts) work simultaneously on three computer screens.
Audadx invests $90 million annually to develop these databases.
Every month, 2.5 million data are recorded, and customers receive updates every two days.
The development of this huge flow of information allows these companies to give them different uses and to offer various products.
The most common application is repair and maintenance, but depending on the country, there are also tools for handling the parts of a car or for calculating the venal or residual value of a car.
