Garage quote in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, Audadx ensures that the user gets a quote in just four steps: identify the vehicle, look for the spare part, create a quote and generate it.
Ease of use is an essential element of these systems, especially to convince older professionals who, to a greater or lesser extent, are reluctant to use new management techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, including 666 passenger cars, 109 all-terrains, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Naturally, to use it, a computer and an Internet connection are necessary.
Once the model to be repaired is identified with its chassis number, a real graphic image of the model in question appears and the necessary part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of the labor, increases or discounts, then he can print the quote to give it to the customer.
AudaWorker is not an estimation tool like AudaPlus, but a catalogue of references.
The main difference between these two systems is that the one intended for garages does not include estimated labour time.
The cost of using this tool for the garage is 350 euros per year, which can be credited.
Currently, Audatex is working to ensure that these images are in three dimensions.
This is an innovation that mechanics see with a very good eye, since it will allow, for example, to select a door and turn it around to see the inner face.
